Tutorial materials for jQuery / Javascript core skills session at Dev8D 2012

The intent is that this directory will contain all software and samples 
needed to conduct the session offline.  These can be downloaded as a ZIP
file via the github "ZIP" tab for the repository.


Part 1: Javascript intro and basics??


Part 2: Basic jQuery (code and slides)
1-1. Hello world
1-2. Hello world personalized - simple content manipulation
1-3. Hello world styled - simple style manipulation
1-4. Functions - breaking out jQuery handler functions and jQuery objects
1-5. Selectors - different simple content selectors
1-6. Modularizing jQuery code; (organization, $, namespaces)
     - http://docs.jquery.com/Using_jQuery_with_Other_Libraries
1-7. Simple dynamic page content (hiding sections)


Part 4: ??


Part 4: Further jQuery (code only for these)
3-1: Fully dynamic page content
3-2: Ajax calls (and same-origin restriction)
     - 08-Roadworks.html
     - Note use of file: URIs to avoid same-origin problems and uncertain network
     - Should work just as well if all files loaded from HTTP server
     - Use of proxying is one technique to combine app on one server with data from another
3-3: Multi-stage call-backs
     - 09-RoadworksUnplanned.html
     - This is a simple example, probably not the best way; hard to compose functions
     - See also: mochikit Deferred (jQuery has something similar), and monad-inspired 
3-4: Using plugins
     - 10-RoadworksCollapser.html
     - Example of using a plugin
     - http://archive.plugins.jquery.com/projects/plugins
     - http://www.aakashweb.com/resources/pages/demos/jquery-collapser/
3-5: Creating plugins
3-6: jQuery-associated data
     - 11-RoadworksSelectorPlugin.html
     - http://docs.jquery.com/Plugins/Authoring    
3-7: qunit: jQuery unit testing
     - 12-SelectorPluginTests.html
     - http://docs.jquery.com/QUnit


